objects.name: infinite second
objects.description: A PowerShell script that deploys ComRAT malware, using multiple layers of obfuscation and modifying the scheduled task of the Microsoft Consolidator to achieve persistence.

objects.name: comrat
objects.description: A malware payload dropped by Infinite Second, available in 32-bit and 64-bit versions.

objects.name: Infinite Second
objects.description: Not explicitly mentioned as a threat actor, but rather as a malware.

objects.name: T1059.001
objects.description: Infinite Second is a PowerShell script that deploys and sets up persistence for ComRAT.

objects.name: T1053.005
objects.description: Infinite Second creates or modifies a scheduled task to run as SYSTEM to launch ComRAT.

objects.name: T1112
objects.description: Infinite Second stores cryptographic keys, additional scripts, and obfuscated payloads in the registry.

objects.name: T1140
objects.description: Infinite Second deobfuscates information stored in the registry using 3DES, XOR, and Base64 encoding.

objects.name: T1036.005
objects.description: Infinite Second uses registry values that masquerade as legitimate software.

objects.name: T1070.004
objects.description: Infinite Second deletes C:\Windows\Temp\tmp4071.tmp and C:\Users\Public\Documents\thumbs.ini.

objects.name: infinitesecond_random_name_function
objects.description: YARA rule to detect related activity.
objects.pattern: rule infinitesecond_random_name_function { meta: author = "NCSC" description = "Identifies the random name generator" strings: $ = "function TVM730egf([string[]]$GP50afa) { $UC33gfa = ((1..(Get-Random -Min 2 -Max 4) | % {[Char](Get-Random -Min 0x41 -Max 0x5B)}) -join '');" $ = "$EQ33abh = ((1..(Get-Random -Min 2 -Max 4) | % {[Char](Get-Random -Min 0x30 -Max 0x3A)}) -join '');" $ = "$OFK689fa = ((1..(Get-Random -Min 2 -Max 4) | % {[Char](Get-Random -Min 0x61 -Max 0x6B)}) -join '');" condition: any of them }

objects.name: infinitesecond_hardcoded_strings
objects.description: YARA rule to detect related activity.
objects.pattern: rule infinitesecond_hardcoded_strings { meta: author = "NCSC" description = "Identifies hardcoded strings throughout the script" strings: $ = "HKLM:\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\SQMClient\Windows" $ = "\\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\WINEVT\Publishers\{cabe18a5-69b9-4e2-bed0-fa080ed05a3b}\ChannelReferences\0" $ = "C:\Windows\Temp\tmp4071.tmp" $ = "C:\Windows\System32\Tasks\Microsoft\Windows\Customer Experience Improvement Program\Consolidator" $ = "Microsoft\Windows\Customer Experience Improvement Program" $ = "WSqmConHex" $ = "WSqmConBin" $ = "WSqmCons" $ = "WSqmConBak" condition: 4 of them }

objects.name: infinitesecond_3des_file
objects.description: YARA rule to detect related activity.
objects.pattern: rule infinitesecond_3des_file { meta: author = "NCSC" description = "3DES Initialisation Vector" strings: $IV = "FVADRCORAOSKBHPX" condition: all of them }

objects.name: infinitesecond_psbreakpoint_luis_armstrong
objects.description: YARA rule to detect related activity.
objects.pattern: rule infinitesecond_psbreakpoint_luis_armstrong { meta: author = "NCSC" description = "Identification of unusual PowerShell break point" strings: $ = "Set-PSBreakpoint -Variable luis_armstrong -Mode Write;" wide ascii condition: all of them }

objects.name: infinitesecond_powershell_reflective_injection
objects.description: YARA rule to detect related activity.
objects.pattern: rule infinitesecond_powershell_reflective_injection { meta: author = "NCSC" description = "Identifies a modification made to reflective injection script" strings: $process_number = {7b 54 68 72 6f 77 20 22 43 61 6e 27 74 20 66 69 6e 64 20 70 72 6f 63 65 73 73 20 24 50 72 6f 63 4e 61 6d 65 22 7d 65 6c 73 65 7b 24 50 72 6f 63 49 64 20 3d 20 24 50 72 6f 63 65 73 73 65 73 5b 30 5d 2e 49 44 7d 7d} // {Throw "Can't find process $ProcName"}else{$ProcId = $Processes[0].ID}} condition: all of them }
